def: A weakening or cessation of the contractile power of the heart.

That which enters into a compound, or is a component part ofany combination or mixture; an element; a constituent.By way of analysis we may proceed from compounds to ingredients. SirI. Newton.Water is the chief ingredient in all the animal fluids and solids.Arbuthnot.
The office or jurisdiction of a matriarch; a matriarchal formof government.
The hard pearly internal layer of several kinds of shells, esp.of pearl oysters, river mussels, and the abalone shells; nacre. SeePearl.
One who, or that which, adjusts.
One of the large scales on the belly of a serpent.
Cutting; divivding into two parts; as, a secant line.

A piece, usually a plate, applied to a sliding piece, toreceive wear and afford a means of adjustment; -- also called shoe,and gib. Slipper animalcule (Zoöl.), a ciliated infusorian of thegenus Paramecium.-- Slipper flower.(Bot.) Slipperwort.-- Slipper limpet, or Slipper shell (Zoöl.), a boat shell.
